headlines.description: — Tennessee Titans rookie quarterback Will Levis needed a moment to reflect after a 20-16 loss to the Pittsburgh Steelers on Thursday night – his first loss in the NFL.
headlines.shortLinkText: Titans rookie Levis reflects after first NFL loss vs. Steelers

events.name: Miami Dolphins at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: — Patrick Mahomes said teammate Bryan Cook looked as if he was running the anchor leg of a 4x100-meter track and field relay on his touchdown.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes throws 2 TDs and Chiefs hang on to beat Dolphins 21-14 in Germany

headlines.description: — Joshua Dobbs hadn't had time to learn his new Minnesota teammates' names in his five days with the team, much less figure out the playbook.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dobbs rallies Vikings to 31-28 victory over the Falcons 5 days after being acquired in a trade

headlines.description: — Deshaun Watson reared back and in one motion signaled his return.
headlines.shortLinkText: Deshaun Watson throws 2 TD passes in return from shoulder injury, Browns demolish Cardinals 27-0

events.name: Los Angeles Rams at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: — Aaron Jones finally ended the Green Bay Packers' first-half touchdown drought.
headlines.shortLinkText: Packers snap 4-game skid with 20-3 victory over struggling Rams

events.name: Washington Commanders at New England Patriots

headlines.shortLinkText: Jartavius Martin's late interception helps Commanders stun Patriots 20-17

events.name: Chicago Bears at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: — Taysom Hill's production near the goal line put him in Hall-of-Fame company, and defensive back Paulson Adebo had what he considered the game of his life.
headlines.shortLinkText: Taysom Hill's TDs receiving and passing, Paulson Adebo's takeaways lift Saints past Bears 24-17

headlines.description: — The Baltimore Ravens let the trade deadline pass without adding a running back.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ravens rout Seahawks 37-3 behind defense and Keaton Mitchell's big day

events.name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Houston Texans

headlines.description: — Down by four with less than a minute to go Sunday, rookie quarterback C.J. Stroud had complete confidence that he could rally the Houston Texans to a victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stroud has 5 TDs and rookie-record 470 yards passing to lift Texans past Bucs 39-37

headlines.description: — The Indianapolis Colts defense entered Sunday's game reeling after allowing at least 37 points in each of its past three games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kenny Moore's two pick-6s help Colts snap 3-game skid with 27-13 victory over Panthers

events.name: New York Giants at Las Vegas Raiders

headlines.description: — The smell of cigar smoke wafted beyond the locker room door, and there was no doubt the Raiders were at long last enjoying themselves.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raiders roll past Giants 30-6 to give Antonio Pierce a win in his debut as interim coach

headlines.description: — Jalen Hurts feigned memory loss. What raced through his mind when a helmet crashed into his already bruised left knee and sent him hobbling toward the sideline — and sent edgy Eagles fans into several anxious moments?
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Hurts shakes off knee injury and leads Eagles past Cowboys 28-23 for NFL best 8-1 mark

headlines.description: — The Cincinnati Bengals showed a national TV audience on Sunday night they are still serious AFC playoff contenders.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burrow passes for 348 yards and 2 TDs and Bengals' defense clamps down on Bills in 24-18 win

events.name: Los Angeles Chargers at New York Jets

headlines.description: — Justin Herbert and the Los Angeles Chargers' offense didn't have to do much against the New York Jets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chargers roll past Jets 27-6 behind Davis' punt return, Ekeler's 2 TDs and LA's sack-happy defense
